entry.title: Special Weather Statement issued April 24 at 5:54AM AKDT by NWS
entry.summary: ...Significant Snowmelt Across The Southeast Interior This Week... Most of the Southeast Interior saw the depth of snow on the ground drop several inches on Saturday, with high temperatures reaching into the 50s. Today will remain warm with highs in the 50s, and lows in the 20s and lower 30s. Similar conditions are expected for most of next week.
